                  SAturne is happily Placed, when wee finde his Line wholly running to his Region: But leſſe happy, when hee preſents ſome inauſpicious Characters: unhappily, if hee ſhow confuſed, and infortunate Signes. Hee governes the Spleene, Bones, and Bladders. When he is Fortunate hee makes Men ſilent, Provident, of good, and profound Counſells: ſuch as Muſe much, and are ſomewhat ſorrowfull; 


Men that are puft up with a ſilent ſpirit, and whoſe aime is at Honours. And theſe are ſlender of Body, ſomewhat tall, pale and feeble, their haire blackiſh, Eyes hollow:
they are fortunate in tilling of ground, and in mettalls of all ſorts, yet more careleſſe of their Wives, and leſſe addicted to Venery; fooliſhly laughing, and jeaſting: tenacious alſo, and more worldly then is fitting or juſt, &c.
